commit.message: Check for sunrise-prior-window-configuration before setting it

Work on redoing pane management some more

The 'left and 'right panes are now called 'a and 'b since in addition
to the usual horizontal pane layout, Sunrise can do vertical and
one-pane layouts.

Get rid of sunrise-running

This commit also fixes a regression a couple commits back that caused
`M-x sunrise` to no longer put its dired buffers into sunrise-mode.

Fix infinite loop in pane setup

This could be triggered by M-x sunrise. Caused by the recent change
from the sunrise-running variable to the sunrise-running-p function.

Drop C-e and C-y scroll key bindings (#80)

According to Emacs conventions, these are reserved keys that should
not be bound by a major mode.

Add more robust check for window layout (#109)

Manually setting variables such as `sunrise-running` is brittle in
practice. Try to get a more reliable result by analyzing the Emacs
frame's window layout afresh each time `sunrise-running-p` is called.

Refactor sunrise-running

- Instead of reading the value of the sunrise-running variable
  directly, code now calls `(sunrise-running-p)`.

- In the future, drop the variable altogether and make the function
  infer from scratch whether or not Sunrise is running each time it's
  called.
Fix other-window error in nativecomp Emacs (#108)
